        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Well I really don't put much value on int.  Think of int as how big of a gas tank you have.  Lots of int is nice in that your mana goes farther, but you still use the same amount.  HPs are what allows you to actually make more mana.  If you have lots of hps, you can lich down far enough to make effective use of Bond of Death without risking your life by pulling with 400 hps.  Its all about mana regen, not max mana imo.</P><P> My advice to you is to just buy Black Sapphire stuff with your pp.  By getting 2 BS earrings and a BS necklace, you will add 135 hps and actually gain mana.  Reason why is at 33 you are only getting 7-8 mana per int point. The 16 int you have right now there would only be around 115-120 mana.  With the BS youll get 135 direct mana. Also might wanna pick up a spider fur belt.  They are cheap, like 250 and you get 40hps.</P><P><b><font color=blue>Retrievil Hesevil</font id=blue></b><BR><font color=red><b>58 DE Necromancer - Tallon Zek</font id=red></b><BR><font color=blue><b>50 Iksar Necromancer - Rodcet Nife</b></font id=blue><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=333155" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=333155</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
